[Lock Clicks]

53:58.904 --> 54:01.822
[Lock Rattling]

54:01.907 --> 54:04.909
[Explosions Continue]

54:14.711 --> 54:16.712
This way,
Mr. Dussel.

54:20.592 --> 54:24.678
[Siren Droning]

54:31.353 --> 54:34.355
[Siren Winding Down]

54:44.240 --> 54:46.742
[Siren Fades]

55:08.974 --> 55:11.934
[Knocking]

55:12.018 --> 55:15.604
It is Kraler.
Please open.
And Miep.

55:15.689 --> 55:17.690
[Mrs. Van Daan]
Oh, bless them.
They are here.

55:17.774 --> 55:22.069
- [Mr. Frank] Kraler?
- [Kraler]
And Miep, yes. Open, please.

55:26.282 --> 55:30.911
Well, we had
a visitor last night.
A visitor last night?

55:30.996 --> 55:32.663
Yes, yes.
A thief.

55:32.747 --> 55:34.540
It was a thief?
Did you
hear him?

55:34.624 --> 55:36.458
Yes, we heard him.
He was
right under you.

55:36.543 --> 55:39.336
- In the office right under here.
- We did not know.

55:39.421 --> 55:41.797
[Mrs. Van Daan]
We thought it was
the Green Police.

55:41.923 --> 55:46.677
Are you sure, Miep?
You were, of course,
quiet?

55:46.761 --> 55:50.723
We didn't move.
We hardly breathed
all night.

55:50.849 --> 55:54.852
That is good.
It was close.
Too close.

55:54.936 --> 55:57.271
He went through everything.
The desk and the files.

55:57.355 --> 56:00.941
The desk and the files.
And he found the safe, but
he could not get it open.

56:01.026 --> 56:03.694
He was looking for
our ration card supply
from the Underground.

56:03.778 --> 56:06.071
Somebody knows.
They're in that safe.

56:06.156 --> 56:11.076
They'll come back.
Get rid of that safe.
Get it out of here.

56:11.161 --> 56:13.162
Yes. Put a sign on
the door:

56:13.288 --> 56:17.082
"Burglars, do not come back.
The safe is gone."
Jokes, yet.

56:17.208 --> 56:19.460
Mr. Frank,
I must talk to you.
Yes, of course.

56:19.544 --> 56:21.712
Maybe it's the radio.
We should get rid of
the radio.

56:21.796 --> 56:25.257
Put it in the stove, burn it.
If the Green Police
found that radio-

56:25.341 --> 56:27.342
And they'd find her diary.
We'll burn that too.

56:27.427 --> 56:29.219
Not my diary.

56:29.345 --> 56:32.264
My diary goes,
I go with it.
Where is it?

56:32.348 --> 56:35.476
If they find us,
they might just as well
find the diary, the radio.

56:35.560 --> 56:37.019
What'll be
the difference?

56:37.020 --> 56:37.436
What'll be
the difference?

56:37.562 --> 56:40.773
Usually, when I come up here,
I try to bring good news.
Yes, I know.

56:40.857 --> 56:43.358
Something has happened.
A man came to me.

56:43.443 --> 56:46.361
He told me that
he has a Jewish friend- a dentist.

56:46.446 --> 56:50.365
He begged me,
could I find him a hiding place?
So I have come to you.

56:50.450 --> 56:53.744
I know it is a terrible thing to ask,
living the way you are,

56:53.828 --> 56:56.830
but could you take him in?

56:56.915 --> 57:00.084
Well, of course
we will.
His name is Jan Dussel.

57:00.168 --> 57:04.588
Dussel. Wait a minute.
I think I know him.
It's fine to have him.

57:04.672 --> 57:07.424
But, Otto, where are
we going to put him? Where?

57:07.509 --> 57:09.718
There's so little food as it is,
and to take in another person-

57:09.803 --> 57:11.720
We can stretch the food
a little, Mr. Van Daan.

57:11.846 --> 57:14.431
He can have my bed.
No, thank you, Peter.

57:14.516 --> 57:16.975
Margot will move
in here with us,
and he can have her bed.

57:17.060 --> 57:20.395
- I'll get my things out.
- [Footsteps Descending]

57:47.382 --> 57:50.384
[Bell Tolling]

57:59.561 --> 58:01.520
Mr. Dussel.

58:10.738 --> 58:13.407
[Tolling Continues]
Don't bump your head.

58:16.703 --> 58:20.330
Come in, Mr. Dussel.

58:20.415 --> 58:24.084
This is Mr. Frank.
Mr. Otto Frank?

58:24.169 --> 58:26.837
Yes. Let me have
your things, please.

58:26.921 --> 58:30.507
Thank you, Mr. Frank.
I leave you in good hands.

58:30.592 --> 58:32.342
Mr. Dussel?
Hmm?

58:32.427 --> 58:35.095
I must return
your coat.

58:36.973 --> 58:39.266
What can I say to thank you?

58:39.350 --> 58:43.228
Mr. Kraler and Miep,
they're our lifeline.
Without them, we couldn't live.

58:43.313 --> 58:46.106
Please, you make us
seem very heroic.
It isn't that at all.

58:46.232 --> 58:51.111
We simply don't like the Nazis.
We don't like their methods-
I know. I know.

58:51.196 --> 58:53.864
"Nobody's gonna tell
us Dutchmen what to do
with our damn Jews."

58:53.948 --> 58:57.993
[Chuckles] We will be
up tomorrow to see that
they are treating you right.

58:58.119 --> 59:01.955
Good-bye.
[Mr. Frank] Good-bye, Mr. Kraler.
Good-bye, Miep.

59:02.081 --> 59:05.209
Welcome, Mr. Dussel.
Thank you.

59:05.293 --> 59:08.921
This is my wife, Edith.
Mr. and Mrs. Van Daan.

59:09.005 --> 59:13.467
Their son, Peter,
my daughters Margot and Anne.

59:13.593 --> 59:15.928
Anne.
How do you do.

59:16.054 --> 59:20.807
Margot.
Please, Mr. Dussel,
sit down.

59:21.809 --> 59:24.519
Thank you.

59:24.604 --> 59:27.272
I'm dreaming,
I know it.

59:27.357 --> 59:30.651
Mr. Otto Frank, here.

59:30.735 --> 59:35.322
You're not in Switzerland, then?
Someone said that
you escaped to Switzerland.

59:37.283 --> 59:40.953
And you've been here
all this time?
Ever since July.

59:43.289 --> 59:47.251
Did Mr. Kraler warn you
you won't get much to eat here?

59:47.335 --> 59:52.506
You can imagine...
three ration cards
among the seven of us.

59:52.590 --> 59:55.926
Now you make eight.

59:56.010 --> 59:59.471
Mr. Van Daan, you don't realize
what's happening outside...

59:59.555 --> 01:00:02.224
that you should warn me
of a thing like that.

01:00:03.685 --> 01:00:08.355
You don't realize what's going on
right here in Amsterdam.

01:00:08.439 --> 01:00:10.649
Every day, hundreds
of Jews disappear.

01:00:13.027 --> 01:00:17.656
They surround a block,
and they search
house by house.

01:00:19.409 --> 01:00:24.079
Every day children
come home from school
to find their parents gone.

01:00:25.415 --> 01:00:27.416
Hundreds are being deported.

01:00:30.003 --> 01:00:33.672
People that you and I know-
the Hallensteins, the Wessels.

01:00:33.756 --> 01:00:35.674
[Mrs. Van Daan]
Oh, no.

01:00:35.758 --> 01:00:38.802
You get your
call-up notice-

01:00:38.886 --> 01:00:42.848
come to the station
on such and such a day and hour.

01:00:42.932 --> 01:00:45.600
Bring only what
you can carry.

01:00:45.685 --> 01:00:49.104
If you don't go, they come
and drag you from your home...

01:00:49.188 --> 01:00:52.107
and ship you off to Mauthausen-
the death camp.

01:00:52.191 --> 01:00:54.609
We didn't know
that things had got
so much worse.

01:00:54.694 --> 01:00:58.155
Forgive me
for speaking so.

01:00:58.239 --> 01:01:01.450
Do you know the de Vries?

01:01:01.534 --> 01:01:03.535
They're gone.

01:01:09.417 --> 01:01:12.753
Sanne and I
are in the same class.

01:01:12.837 --> 01:01:16.631
Sanne is my best-
my best friend.

01:01:16.716 --> 01:01:20.886
She returned home from school
to find her parents gone.

01:01:23.139 --> 01:01:27.476
She was alone for two days,
and then they came
and took her away.

01:01:30.146 --> 01:01:32.147
Gone?

01:01:38.821 --> 01:01:41.156
With all the others.

01:01:42.784 --> 01:01:45.285
Oh, no.

01:01:51.459 --> 01:01:54.419
Some people named Meyerberg,
they lived near us-

01:01:54.504 --> 01:01:57.047
I think we should
put this off until later,
Mrs. Van Daan.

01:01:57.131 --> 01:01:59.299
I'm sure Mr. Dussel would
like to get settled now.

01:01:59.384 --> 01:02:02.386
Annele, would you like to
take Mr. Dussel to his room?

01:02:02.470 --> 01:02:05.138
If youâ€™ll come with me,
Mr. Dussel.

01:02:07.725 --> 01:02:12.396
Uh, forgive me
if I haven't expressed
my gratitude.

01:02:13.648 --> 01:02:17.651
This has been
such a shock to me.

01:02:17.735 --> 01:02:20.654
I always thought of
myself as Dutch.

01:02:20.738 --> 01:02:23.323
I was born in Holland.

01:02:23.408 --> 01:02:27.411
My father was born
in Holland,
and my grandfather.

01:02:27.495 --> 01:02:31.832
And now after
all these years-

01:02:34.335 --> 01:02:36.837
If you will excuse me.

01:02:40.174 --> 01:02:44.344
